text: I have not watched this film, so I’ll make my comments just based off this trailer. If I’m “judging a book by its cover” or “by its summary”, feel free to correct me if I’m wrong.  It is unfortunate that this film turns such serious and gruesome secret government projects such as “MK Ultra” and “Project Monarch” into a comedy. This project has destroyed thousands of lives. Mind control programming is a serious topic that people still suffer from to this point. They may have only retired the name MK Ultra in the 70s; however, mind control projects were never ended and continue to this day.  The main character in this film appears to be a “Delta” programmed assassin that was activated by a “handler” when the woman enters into the shop and says (what seems to us) random words to him — which is a process known as “triggering” where a mind control subject is triggered into their “alter” state (other programmed personality) and is then ready to play the role they were programmed to play. These “random words” are in actuality an activation code. Just like a password to open an email. This is a password to activate an alternate personality that was programmed into this person. Also, only a handler is usually able to activate the alter personality within the subject. Thus this woman, most likely, has known the main character of the film since he was a child.  From the trailer, I can see that his personality is a “Delta”. A “Delta” programmed subject is a code word for a programmed assassin who can be activated at any time. This person has a programmed alter personality, so he may be just living a regular life without even being aware of his alter personality; however, they also suffer from visions or “voices in their head”, so it is not uncommon for these people to suffer from drug abuse. It’s is interesting that the main character in this film is a drug addict. It fits the script. People that have undergone torturous mind control programing have bipolar disorders that have been synthetically programmed into them.  It’s important to note that mind control programming is even more relevant today than it was when the original project MK Ultra was active. Don’t you ever wonder about how can someone walk into a theater, kill dozens of people, and then when asked about it, he has no recollection of doing it and doesn’t even know why he did it? And also at the same time, he was taking various psychiatric drugs? You probably know who I’m talking about and this is just the example of what we’re not being told about mind control programs.  For those of you being exposed to this for the very first time, I suggest reading this article from the Vigilant Citizen: http://vigilantcitizen.com/hidden-knowledge/origins-and-techniques-of-monarch-mind-control/ This article is a crash course into this topic and there are tons of books that you can read about this topic if you want to get deeper.  Mind control programming is a serious science that has been abused by government scientists since the early to mid 20th century (its origins go into ancient times). This is not funny. Making fun and light of this topic is the same thing as making a comedy about The Holocaust during WWII. The suffering the victims of mind control have gone through with the gruesome and torturous methods that have been executed on them while they were little (primarily foster home) children in order to break their minds before being able to program them, are unspeakable and horrendous. So many souls broken, so many deaths, so much needless suffering.
